  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="4936387">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/4936387/" class="title-link">间谍小说以此为巅峰</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-4936387"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/51015839/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/user_normal.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/51015839/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">jianshenyanglu</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2011-05-06"
      class="main-meta">2011-05-06 05:20:29</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_4936387_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  个人感觉这部作品应该是间谍小说的巅峰之作。非常精彩。在特定的年代下，将CIA和KGB的争斗以及交易活灵活现。尤其是地下活动的描写非常真实。实属佳作。 结尾费利托夫的葬礼上，瑞恩对苏联驻美武官的一席话：“我们都以这样或那样的方式服务于我们的国家”引人深思。

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_4936387_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_4936387_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>

      
  



  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="1993833">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1993833/" class="title-link">相当吸引人的小说</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1993833"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/2441618/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u2441618-1.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/2441618/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">bangge</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2009-04-26"
      class="main-meta">2009-04-26 22:33:22</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1993833_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  汤姆·克兰西的小说是相当吸引人的，他对人物和事件的描述相当细腻，阅读时使人如亲临其境；他对故事的“制造”相当符合逻辑，也往往出人意料，从而引人入胜。  总之，我是有计划收罗汤姆·克兰西的全套小说。  

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 0没用</span>
